text: Rajanya Shah (born February 16, 1974) is an American rower who competed in the 1997, 1998, and 1999 World Rowing Championships, as well as the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney, Australia. Shah was born on February 16, 1974 in Albany, New York. She attended Phillips Exeter Academy, and then Brown University, where she coxed an eight-member team. == References == Category:American female rowers Category:Coxswains (rowing) Category:Brown University alumni Category:Phillips Exeter Academy alumni Category:1974 births Category:Living people Category:Olympic rowers of the United States Category:Rowers at the 2000 Summer Olympics
